Banat (1941–1944).label: Banat
Banat (1941–1944).description: The Banat was a political entity established in 1941 after the occupation and partition of Yugoslavia by the Axis Powers in the historical Banat region. Wikipedia

Basutoland.label: Basutoland
Basutoland.description: Basutoland or officially the Territory of Basutoland, was a British Crown colony established in 1884 after the Cape Colony's inability to control the territory. Wikipedia

German New Guinea.label: German New Guinea
German New Guinea.description: German New Guinea was the first part of the German colonial empire. It was a protectorate from 1884 until 1914 when it fell to Australian forces following the outbreak of the First World War. Wikipedia

Grand Duchy of Berg.label: Grand Duchy of Berg
Grand Duchy of Berg.description: The Grand Duchy of Berg was established by Napoleon Bonaparte after his victory at the 1805 Battle of Austerlitz on territories between the French Empire at the Rhine river and the German Kingdom of Westphalia. Wikipedia

Landgraviate of Hesse.label: Landgraviate of Hesse
Landgraviate of Hesse.description: The Landgraviate of Hesse was a Principality of the Holy Roman Empire. It existed as a unity from 1264 to 1567, when it was divided between the sons of late Landgrave Philip I. Wikipedia

Kingdom of Serbia.label: Kingdom of Serbia
Kingdom of Serbia.description: The Kingdom of Serbia was created when Prince Milan Obrenović, ruler of the Principality of Serbia, was crowned king in 1882. The Principality of Serbia was ruled by the Obrenović dynasty from 1817 onwards. Wikipedia

Government of the Autonomous Republic of.label: Government of the Autonomous Republic of Abkhazia
Government of the Autonomous Republic of.description: The Government of the Autonomous Republic of Abkhazia is an administration recognized by Georgia as the legal government of Abkhazia. Wikipedia

Bishopric of Courland.label: Bishopric of Courland
Bishopric of Courland.description: The Bishopric of Courland was the second smallest ecclesiastical state in the Livonian Confederation founded in the aftermath of the Livonian Crusade. Wikipedia

Grand Duchy of Mecklenburg-Schwerin.label: Grand Duchy of Mecklenburg-Schwerin
Grand Duchy of Mecklenburg-Schwerin.description: The Grand Duchy of Mecklenburg-Schwerin was a territory in Northern Germany held by the House of Mecklenburg residing at Schwerin. Wikipedia

March of Tuscany.label: Margravate of Tuscany
March of Tuscany.description: The March of Tuscia or Margraviate of Tuscany was a frontier march of the Kingdom of Italy and the Holy Roman Empire. Wikipedia

Margraviate of Baden.label: Margraviate of Baden
Margraviate of Baden.description: The Margraviate of Baden was a historical territory of the Holy Roman Empire. Spread along the east side of the Upper Rhine River in southwestern Germany, it was named a margraviate in 1112 and existed ... Wikipedia

Lu (state).label: Lu
Lu (state).description: Lu was a vassal state during the Zhou Dynasty of ancient China. Founded in the 11th century BC, its rulers were from a cadet branch of the House of Ji that ruled the Zhou Dynasty. Wikipedia

Kingdom of Nejd and Hejaz.label: Kingdom of Nejd and Hejaz
Kingdom of Nejd and Hejaz.description: The Kingdom of Nejd and Hejaz was a political union established after the Kingdom of Hejaz had been conquered by the Sultanate of Nejd under Abdul Aziz Ibn Saud in 1925. Wikipedia

Kingdom of Bulgaria.label: Kingdom of Bulgaria
Kingdom of Bulgaria.description: The Kingdom of Bulgaria, also referred to as the Tsardom of Bulgaria, the Third Bulgarian Tsardom and the Third Bulgarian Empire, was a constitutional monarchy, created on 22 September 1908, as а result ... Wikipedia

Grand Duchy of Würzburg.label: Grand Duchy of Würzburg
Grand Duchy of Würzburg.description: The Grand Duchy of Würzburg was a German grand duchy centered on Würzburg existing in the early 19th century. Wikipedia

Khanka Lake.label: Lake Khanka
Khanka Lake.description: Lake Khanka, is a freshwater lake located on the border between Primorsky Krai, Russia and Heilongjiang province, Northeast China. At its closest point, it is situated 79 kilometres east of the city of Jixi, Heilongjiang. Wikipedia

German colonial empire.label: German colonial empire
German colonial empire.description: The German colonial empire was the overseas territories of Imperial Germany. Short-lived colonial efforts by individual German states had occurred in preceding centuries, but colonial efforts only began in 1884. Wikipedia

Kingdom of Saxony.label: Kingdom of Saxony
Kingdom of Saxony.description: The Kingdom of Saxony, lasting between 1806 and 1918, was an independent member of a number of historical confederacies in Napoleonic through post-Napoleonic Germany. From 1871 it was part of the German Empire. Wikipedia

Landgraviate of Hesse-Kassel.label: Landgraviate of Hesse-Kassel
Landgraviate of Hesse-Kassel.description: The Landgraviate of Hesse-Kassel, known as Hesse-Cassel during its existence, was a state in the Holy Roman Empire under Imperial immediacy that came into existence when the Landgraviate of Hesse was ... Wikipedia

Kievan Rus'.label: Kievan Rus'
Kievan Rus'.description: Kievan Rus' was a loose federation of East Slavic tribes in Europe from the late 9th to the mid-13th century, under the reign of the Rurik dynasty. Wikipedia

Kingdom of Dazhou.label: Kingdom of Dazhou
Kingdom of Dazhou.description: Kingdom of Great or Greater Zhou, was a state established in 1354 by Zhang Shicheng, one of the leaders of the Red Turban Rebellion. Kingdom of Dazhou lasted for only 13 years and had only one King. Wikipedia

March of the Nordgau.label: March of the Nordgau
March of the Nordgau.description: The March of the Nordgau or the Bavarian Nordgau was a margraviate in the north of the duchy of Bavaria in the High Middle Ages. It covered the region roughly covered by the modern Upper Palatinate along the river Main. Wikipedia

Free Republic of Schwarzenberg.label: Free Republic of Schwarzenberg
Free Republic of Schwarzenberg.description: The Free Republic of Schwarzenberg is a term now used for an unoccupied area in Western Saxony that existed for several weeks after the German capitulation on May 8, 1945. Wikipedia

K'iche' Kingdom of Q'umarkaj.label: K'iche' Kingdom of Q'umarkaj
K'iche' Kingdom of Q'umarkaj.description: The K'iche' Kingdom of Q'umarkaj was a state in the highlands of modern-day Guatemala which was founded by the K'iche' Maya in the thirteenth century, and which expanded through the fifteenth century ... Wikipedia

Kingdom of Tavolara.label: Kingdom of Tavolara
Kingdom of Tavolara.description: The Kingdom of Tavolara was an imaginary state claiming independence in the 19th and 20th centuries in Tavolara Island, off the northeast coast of Sardinia. Set up by the Bertoleoni family, it claimed to be one of the smallest kingdoms in the world. Wikipedia

Kingdom of Iceland.label: Kingdom of Iceland
Kingdom of Iceland.description: The Kingdom of Iceland was a constitutional monarchy that existed through the Act of Union with Denmark signed on 1 December 1918. It lasted until 17 June 1944 when a national referendum established the Republic of Iceland in its place. Wikipedia

French colonial empire.label: French colonial empire
French colonial empire.description: The French colonial empire was constituted of the overseas colonies, protectorates and mandate territories that came under French rule from the 17th century onward. Wikipedia

Kingdom of Bohemia.label: Kingdom of Bohemia
Kingdom of Bohemia.description: The Kingdom of Bohemia was a state located in the region of Bohemia in Central Europe, whose territory is currently included in the modern-day Czech Republic. Wikipedia

Engelberg Abbey.label: Engelberg Abbey
Engelberg Abbey.description: Engelberg Abbey is a Benedictine monastery in Engelberg, Canton of Obwalden, Switzerland. It was formerly in the Diocese of Constance, but now in the Diocese of Chur. Wikipedia

Kharavela.label: Kharavela
Kharavela.description: Khārabēḷa was the third and greatest emperor of the Mahameghavahana dynasty of Kaḷinga. The main source of information about Khārabeḷa is his famous seventeen line rock-cut Hātigumphā inscription in a cave in the Udayagiri hills near ... Wikipedia

County of Bentheim.label: County of Bentheim
County of Bentheim.description: The County of Bentheim was a state of the Holy Roman Empire, located in the south-west corner of today's Lower Saxony, Germany. The county's borders corresponded largely to those of the modern administrative district of Grafschaft Bentheim. Wikipedia

Duchy of Oświęcim.label: Duchy of Oświęcim
Duchy of Oświęcim.description: The Duchy of Oświęcim, or the Duchy of Auschwitz, was one of many Duchies of Silesia, formed in the aftermath of the fragmentation of Poland. Wikipedia

Islamic Emirate of Afghanistan.label: Islamic Emirate of Afghanistan
Islamic Emirate of Afghanistan.description: The Islamic Emirate of Afghanistan was established in 1996 when the Taliban began their rule of Afghanistan and ended with their fall from power in 2001. Wikipedia

Majapahit.label: Majapahit
Majapahit.description: Majapahit was a vast archipelagic empire based on the island of Java from 1293 to around 1500. Majapahit reached its peak of glory during the era of Hayam Wuruk, whose reign from 1350 to 1389 marked by conquest which extended through Southeast Asia. Wikipedia

Duchy of Krnov.label: Duchy of Krnov
Duchy of Krnov.description: Duchy of Krnov was one of the Duchies of Silesia, with its capital in Krnov, present-day Czech Republic. Wikipedia

Duchy of Bytom.label: Duchy of Bytom
Duchy of Bytom.description: The Duchy of Bytom or Duchy of Beuthen was one of many Silesian duchies. It was established in Upper Silesia about 1281 during the division of the Duchy of Opole and Racibórz among the sons of Duke Władysław Opolski. Wikipedia

County of Sargans.label: County of Sargans
County of Sargans.description: The County of Sargans was a state of the Holy Roman Empire. From 1458 until the French Revolutionary War in 1798, Sargans became a condominium of the Old Swiss Confederacy, administered jointly by the ... Wikipedia

County of Kladsko.label: County of Kladsko
County of Kladsko.description: The County of Kladsko was a historical administrative unit in the Kingdom of Bohemia and later in the Kingdom of Prussia with its capital at Kłodzko on the Nysa river. Wikipedia

Kingdom of Montenegro (1941–1944).label: Kingdom of Montenegro
Kingdom of Montenegro (1941–1944).description: The Italian governorate of Montenegro existed from April 1941 to September 1943 as an occupied territory under military government of Fascist Italy, and was a component of the Italian Empire. Wikipedia

Khedivate of Egypt.label: Khedivate of Egypt
Khedivate of Egypt.description: The Khedivate of Egypt was an autonomous tributary state of the Ottoman Empire, established and ruled by the Muhammad Ali Dynasty following the defeat and expulsion of Napoleon Bonaparte's forces which ... Wikipedia

Freie Ämter.label: Freie Ämter
Freie Ämter.description: The Freiamt or Freie Ämter is a region in Switzerland and is located in the southeast of Canton of Aargau. It comprises the area between the Lindenberg and Heitersberg and from the terminal moraine at Othmarsingen to Reuss river in Dietwil. Wikipedia

Duchy of Jawor.label: Duchy of Jawor
Duchy of Jawor.description: Duchy of Jawor was one of the Duchies of Silesia established in 1274 as a subdivision of the Duchy of Legnica. It was ruled by the Silesian Piasts, with its capital at Jawor in Lower Silesia. Wikipedia

Electorate of Trier.label: Electorate of Trier
Electorate of Trier.description: The Electorate of Trier, traditionally known in English by its French name of Trèves, was an ecclesiastical principality of the Holy Roman Empire that existed from the end of the 9th to the early 19th century. Wikipedia

Dos Pilas.label: Dos Pilas
Dos Pilas.description: Dos Pilas is a Pre-Columbian site of the Maya civilization located in what is now the department of Petén, Guatemala. Wikipedia

County of Sicily.label: County of Sicily
County of Sicily.description: The County of Sicily was a Norman state comprising the islands of Sicily and Malta from 1071 until 1130. The county began to form during the Christian reconquest of Sicily from the Muslim Emirate, established by conquest in 965. Wikipedia

Carantania.label: Carantania
Carantania.description: Carantania, also known as Carentania was a Slavic principality that emerged in the second half of the 7th century, in the territory of present-day southern Austria and north-eastern Slovenia. Wikipedia

Bishopric of Minden.label: Bishopric of Minden
Bishopric of Minden.description: The Bishopric of Minden was a Roman Catholic diocese and a state, Prince-bishopric of Minden, of the Holy Roman Empire. Its capital was Minden which is in modern-day Germany. Wikipedia

Chu (state).label: Chu
Chu (state).description: Chu was an ancient Chinese state in the Yangtze valley during the Zhou Dynasty. Originally Chu was considered a viscounty but, starting from King Wu in the early 8th century BC, the rulers of Chu declared ... Wikipedia

Bishopric of Halberstadt.label: Bishopric of Halberstadt
Bishopric of Halberstadt.description: The Bishopric of Halberstadt was a Roman Catholic diocese and a state within the Holy Roman Empire, the Prince-bishopric of Halberstadt. Its capital was Halberstadt in present-day Saxony-Anhalt, north of the Harz mountain range, Germany. Wikipedia

Duchy of Zator.label: Duchy of Zator
Duchy of Zator.description:
The Duchy of Zator was one of many Duchies of Silesia.
It was split off the Duchy of Oświęcim, when after eleven years of joint rule the sons of Duke Casimir I in 1445 finally divided the lands among ... Wikipedia

Bishopric of Utrecht.label: Bishopric of Utrecht
Bishopric of Utrecht.description:
The Bishopric of Utrecht is a diocese based in the Dutch city of Utrecht.
From 1024 until 1528, it was one of the Prince-Bishoprics of the Holy Roman Empire, constituting, in addition to its eccleaiastical aspect, a civil state within the Empire. Wikipedia

Federal State of Austria.label: Federal State of Austria
Federal State of Austria.description: The Federal State of Austria refers to Austria between 1934 and 1938 while it was a single-party state led by the clerico-fascist Fatherland's Front. Wikipedia

Bishopric of Lübeck.label: Bishopric of Lübeck
Bishopric of Lübeck.description: The Bishopric of Lübeck was a Roman-Catholic and, later, Protestant diocese, as well as a state of the Holy Roman Empire. Wikipedia

Kingdom of Prussia.label: Kingdom of Prussia
Kingdom of Prussia.description: The Kingdom of Prussia was a German kingdom that existed between 1701 and 1918 and included parts of present-day Germany, Poland, Russia, Lithuania, Denmark, Belgium and the Czech Republic. Wikipedia

Democratic Republic of Afghanistan.label: Democratic Republic of Afghanistan
Democratic Republic of Afghanistan.description: The Democratic Republic of Afghanistan, renamed in 1987 to the Republic of Afghanistan, existed from 1978 to 1992 and covers the period when the communist People's Democratic Party of Afghanistan ruled Afghanistan. Wikipedia

Duchy of Brzeg.label: Duchy of Brzeg
Duchy of Brzeg.description:
The Duchy of Brzeg or Duchy of Brieg, was one of the Duchies of Silesia. Its capital was Brzeg.
It was created in 1311 during the fragmentation of the Duchy of Legnica among the sons of Duke Henry V ... Wikipedia

Deccan sultanates.label: Deccan sultanates
Deccan sultanates.description: The Deccan sultanates were five Turkic ruled late medieval kingdoms, namely, Bijapur, Golkonda, Ahmednagar, Bidar, and Berar in south-western India. Wikipedia

Archbishopric of Riga.label: Archbishopric of Riga
Archbishopric of Riga.description: The Archbishopric of Riga was an archbishopric in Medieval Livonia, a subject to the Holy See. It was established in 1186 as the bishopric of Livonia at Üxküll, then after moving to Riga it became the ... Wikipedia

Kingdom of Sussex.label: Kingdom of Sussex
Kingdom of Sussex.description: The kingdom of the South Saxons, today referred to as the Kingdom of Sussex, was a Saxon colony and later independent kingdom of the Saxons, on the south coast of England. Wikipedia

Kingdom of Bavaria.label: Kingdom of Bavaria
Kingdom of Bavaria.description: The Kingdom of Bavaria was a German state that existed from 1806 to 1918. The Bavarian Elector Maximilian IV Joseph of the House of Wittelsbach became the first King of Bavaria in 1806 as Maximilian I Joseph. Wikipedia

Allied-occupied Austria.label: Allied-occupied Austria
Allied-occupied Austria.description: The Allied occupation of Austria lasted from 1945 to 1955. Austria had been regarded by Nazi Germany as a constituent part of the German state, but in 1943 the Allied powers agreed in the Declaration ... Wikipedia

Bishopric of Lebus.label: Bishopric of Lebus
Bishopric of Lebus.description: The Bishopric of Lebus was a Roman Catholic diocese of Poland and later an ecclesiastical territory of the Holy Roman Empire. It existed from 1125 until 1598. Wikipedia

Duchy of Courland and Semigallia (1918).label: Duchy of Courland and Semigallia
Duchy of Courland and Semigallia (1918).description: The Duchy of Courland and Semigallia was briefly a client state of the German Empire. It was proclaimed on 8 March 1918, in German-occupied Courland Governorate by a Landesrat composed of Baltic Germans, ... Wikipedia

Bishopric of Dorpat.label: Bishopric of Dorpat
Bishopric of Dorpat.description: The Bishopric of Dorpat was a medieval principality and a catholic diocese which existed from 1224 to 1558, generally encompassing what are now Tartu, Põlva, Võru and Jõgeva counties in Estonia. The Bishopric was part of Livonian Confederation. Wikipedia

County of Sponheim.label: County of Sponheim
County of Sponheim.description: The County of Sponheim was an independent territory in the Holy Roman Empire which lasted from the 11th century until the early 19th century. The name comes from the municipality of Sponheim, where the counts had their original residence. Wikipedia

Bishopric of Worms.label: Bishopric of Worms
Bishopric of Worms.description: The Bishopric of Worms was an ecclesiastical principality of the Holy Roman Empire. Located on both banks of the Rhine around Worms just north of the union of that river with the Neckar, it was largely surrounded by the Electorate of the Palatinate. Wikipedia

Allied-occupied Germany.label: Allied-occupied Germany
Allied-occupied Germany.description: The Allied powers who defeated Nazi Germany in World War II asserted governmental authority over all territory of the German Reich which lay west of the Oder–Neisse line, having formally abolished the German government of Adolf Hitler. Wikipedia

Alamannia.label: Alamannia
Alamannia.description: Alamannia or Alemannia was the territory inhabited by the Germanic Alemanni after they broke through the Roman limes in 213. Wikipedia

Kaisheim Abbey.label: Kaisheim Abbey
Kaisheim Abbey.description:
The Imperial Abbey of Kaisersheim, was a Cistercian monastery in Kaisersheim, Bavaria, Germany.
As one of the 40-odd self-ruling imperial abbeys of the Holy Roman Empire, Kaisersheim was a virtually independent state. Wikipedia

Austrian Littoral.label: Austrian Littoral
Austrian Littoral.description:
The Austrian Littoral was established as a crown land of the Austrian Empire in 1849.
Kingdom of Italy, rewarded for changing sides in the First World War, annexed it according to the secret Treaty of London and later Treaty of Rapallo. Wikipedia

Burgundian Netherlands.label: Burgundian Netherlands
Burgundian Netherlands.description: In the history of the Low Countries, the Burgundian Netherlands were a number of Imperial and French fiefs ruled in personal union by the House of Valois-Burgundy and their Habsburg heirs in the period from 1384 to 1482. Wikipedia
